e supportive Mimamorugai, escalating into a full-fledged war come the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SchoolFestival" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SchoolFestival">School Festival</a>.</li><li> Kanade's hiccups in Episode 11. Turns out she was trolling again.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsNotMyGirlfriend" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsNotMyGirlfriend">She Is Not My Girlfriend</a>:<ul><li> Jiro gets questioned on Subaru's relationship with him by her father while they're in the public bath in episode 8. Jiro vehemently denies being anything more than just classmates and friends. Which causes Subaru, who's hiding right behind him, to let off an annoyed grunt. She also seems rather unhappy in the next scene, which then prompts her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FalseStart" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FalseStart">False Start</a> comment at the end of the episode.</li><li> Towards the end of episode 7, he is forced to tell Subaru about what he did at Usami's apartment, and reassure her that they weren't dating.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a>:<ul><li> When Jiro wakes up strapped to a bed, Kanade tells him he has <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRider" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRider">been turned into a cyborg</a>. He responds with a henshin pose.</li><li> One of Kureha's wrestling moves on Jiro early on is the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Wrestling/BretHart" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Wrestling/BretHart">Sharpshooter</a>.</li><li> In the third chapter of the manga: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JoJosBizarreAdventure" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JoJosBizarreAdventure">Jojo's Unique Adventure?</a></li><li> The S4's appearance is similar to the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/BakaAndTestSummonTheBeasts" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/BakaAndTestSummonTheBeasts">FFF</a>.</li><li> In episode 4's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeCatch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeCatch">Eye Catch</a> Subaru thinks that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Mahoromatic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Mahoromatic">dirty thoughts are bad</a>.</li><li> When an angry Subaru threw Nakuru's Jiro x Subaru yaoi BL out the window, the latter leaps after it screaming "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/GroundControlToPsychoelectricGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/GroundControlToPsychoelectricGirl">I can fly!</a>".</li><li> Episode 10's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OnTheNext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OnTheNext">preview</a> has Jiro declaring "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Oreimo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Oreimo">There's No Way My Little Sister Can Be Wearing Such Cute Panties</a>!", and Kureha replying "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/IDontLikeYouAtAllBigBrother" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/IDontLikeYouAtAllBigBrother">I Don't Care About My Big Brother's Underwear At All!</a>" Bonus points <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KanaHanazawa" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/KanaHanazawa">her seiyuu</a> is Kuroneko</li><li> In episode 10 the game makers have a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Kampfer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/Kampfer">K&auml;mpfer</a>, a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/AriaTheScarletAmmo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/AriaTheScarletAmmo">Aria the Scarlet Ammo</a> and a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/YumekuiMerry" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/YumekuiMerry">Yumekui Merry</a> poster. In the very same episode the game Kanade gave Usami is a reference to <a class="urllink" href="http://